independent.name: Independents
independent.grants: The faceless man the ability to take on other personas. If Jaqen kills a Character, they join this House’s Roster

meereen.name: Council of Meereen
meereen.grants: Knowledge of all diplomatic missions against this House

tyrell.name: House Tyrell
tyrell.grants: Full Secrecy. Missions are never revealed. Not even to the Council of Mereen

arryn.name: House Arryn
arryn.grants: Chance of recovering intel from the source of diplomatic missions run against this house - Chance is 50%, intel at same level as the mission

nightswatch.name: Night’s Watch & Free Folk
nightswatch.grants: Dissemination of misinformation. Chance of false intel to be recovered in diplomatic missions run against this house is 50%

greyjoy.name: House Greyjoy
greyjoy.grants: Theon splatter damage. On a succesful attack by Theon,all characters of the other roster take 5% damage

stark.name: House Stark
stark.grants: Assitance from the Northmen - An addition Level 3 diplomatic mission is run each episode against a random House on this House’s behest

targaryen.name: House Targaryen & Dothraki
targaryen.grants: All Characters on this House’s Roster gain 5% Bonus on a succesful attack by a Dothraki Character

lannister.name: House Lannister
lannister.grants: All performance penalties for running missions are waived - The debts have been paid.

minor.name: League of Minor Orders
minor.grants: Characters with Prominence Power 1 and 2, now multiply their Score with 5 and 6 instead of 4 and 5

bolton.name: House Bolton
bolton.grants: Chance that an attack on this House backfires and retargets the assassin itself - Chance is 15% ∗ target’s prominence power

martell.name: House Martell
martell.grants: All attacks to become lethal, provided that the total prominence power of this House is lower than the prominence of the target’s roster

dickontarly.bio: The younger brother of Samwell Tarly. He became their father Randyll Tarly's heir after he disinherited Samwell by forcing him to join the Night's Watch.
dickontarly.name: Dickon Tarly

branstark.bio: He is the fourth child and second son of Eddard and Catelyn Stark. One of the few characters known to possess magical abilities such as receiving prophetic visions and sending his consciousness into the mind of an animal.
branstark.name: Bran Stark

highsparrow.bio: The High Sparrow is the leader of the religious sect known as the Sparrows and the newly appointed High Septon.Although the High Sparrow seems a harmless old man, he has a will of steel.
highsparrow.name: The High Sparrow

jonsnow.bio: The bastard son of Lord Eddard Stark of Winterfell. He was a steward in the Night's Watch. Served on the Wall as Lord Commander.
jonsnow.name: Jon Snow

walderfrey.bio: Joined forces with the Lannisters and Roose Bolton to betray the Starks, and presided over the gruesome bloodbath of the Red Wedding with palpable glee.
walderfrey.name: Walder Frey

petyrbaelish.bio: Popularly called Littlefinger, a skilled manipulator and uses his ownership of brothels in King's Landing to both accrue intelligence on political rivals and acquire vast wealth.
petyrbaelish.name: Petyr Baelish

yezzanzoqaggaz.bio: A slave-trader from the city of Meereen, on the coast of Slaver's Bay, and one of the Great Masters, the former ruling elite of the city. Purchases and trains pit fighters.
yezzanzoqaggaz.name: Yezzan zo Qaggaz

aryastark.bio: Arya Stark is the youngest daughter and third child of Lady Catelyn and Lord Eddard Stark. Serving Jaqen H'qar at the House of Black and White to become one of the faceless assassins. Currently blind.
aryastark.name: Arya Stark

smalljonumber.bio: Smalljon is the son of Greatjon Umber, the Lord of Last Hearth and proud bannerman of House Stark.
smalljonumber.name: Smalljon Umber

gilly.bio: Gilly is one of the Free Folk, and is a daughter and wife of Craster. In romantic relations with Samwell Tarly.
gilly.name: Gilly

bowenmarsh.bio: Bowen Marsh is the First Steward of the Night's Watch, in charge of the day-to-day running of it. He takes part in and helps to organize a mutiny against Jon Snow.
bowenmarsh.name: Bowen Marsh

yaragreyjoy.bio: Fierce Ironborn warrior commanding her own longship, Theon Greyjoy's older sister and only surviving sibling
yaragreyjoy.name: Yara Greyjoy

unella.bio: Unella is a Septa of the Faith of the Seven and a devoted follower of the High Sparrow. She was in charge of coercing Cersei to "confess".
unella.name: Unella

davosseaworth.bio: Davos is a landed knight, and a former smuggler who was in the service of Stannis Baratheon, Lord of Dragonstone and claimant to the Iron Throne, whom he serves as Hand of the King.
davosseaworth.name: Davos Seaworth

tormundgiantsbane.bio: He is a renowned leader and raider among the Free Folk and second in command behind Mance Rayder
tormundgiantsbane.name: Tormund Giantsbane

waldabolton.bio: She is the new wife of Roose Bolton, the Lord of the Dreadfort.
waldabolton.name: Walda Bolton

macetyrell.bio: The Lord of Highgarden and head of House Tyrell. He is the father of Loras and Margaery Tyrell, and the son of Olenna Tyrell.
macetyrell.name: Mace Tyrell

doranmartell.bio: Prince of Dorne and the Lord of Sunspear. He is the head of House Martell, the ruling house of Dorne, and the older brother of the late Princess Elia.
doranmartell.name: Doran Martell

tallatarly.bio: Talla is sister of Samwell Tarly, and daughter of Lord Randyll Tarly of Horn Hill.
tallatarly.name: Talla Tarly

walderrivers.bio: Known as "Black Walder" for his temper and demeanor. He is a bastard son of his namesake Lord Walder Frey, Lord of the Crossing and head of House Frey. Murdered Catelyn Stark.
walderrivers.name: Walder Rivers

tyenesand.bio: Tyene Sand is the third of the eight bastard daughters of Prince Oberyn Martell, known as the "Sand Snakes".
tyenesand.name: Tyene Sand

samwelltarly.bio: Samwell is a steward in the Night's Watch and is Jon Snow's closest friend.
samwelltarly.name: Samwell Tarly

tyrionlannister.bio: Tyrion Lannister is the youngest son of Lord Tywin Lannister and younger brother of Cersei and Jaime Lannister. A dwarf, he uses his wit and intellect to overcome the prejudice he faces.
tyrionlannister.name: Tyrion Lannister

razdalmoeraz.bio: Razdal mo Eraz is a wealthy Yunkish slave-trader, one of the Wise Masters, the ruling elite of the city. Razdal is not a braggart, but shrewd and politically savvy. A reserved, calculating man, he is capable of being polite when it is politically expedient.
razdalmoeraz.name: Razdal mo Eraz

hodor.bio: Hodor is a simpleminded servant of House Stark at Winterfell, currently guardian of Bran Stark, journeying beyond the wall to find the Three-eyed raven appearing in Bran's dreams.
hodor.name: Hodor

varys.bio: Varys is a eunuch and was the Master of Whisperers on the King's Small Council until he is forced to flee King's Landing with Tyrion Lannister
varys.name: Varys

yohnroyce.bio: Lord of Runestone, where he fosters Robin Arryn, and a powerful bannerman of House Arryn.
yohnroyce.name: Yohn Royce

threeeyedraven.bio: Under the guise of a three-eyed raven, he appears in Bran Stark's vision-dreams, following his fall and injury, prompting his quest beyond the Wall and guiding him to the cave in which his real human body resides.
threeeyedraven.name: Three Eyed Raven

kinvara.bio: Kinvara is a Red Priestess, one of the high-ranking leaders in the religion of R'hllor, the Lord of Light. Her full title is "High Priestess of the Red Temple of Volantis, the Flametruth, the Light of Wisdom, and First Servant of the Lord of Light".
kinvara.name: Kinvara

jaqenhghar.bio: An assumed identity of one of the Faceless Men of Braavos, a feared order of mysterious assassins with the ability to change their appearance at will.
jaqenhghar.name: Jaqen H'ghar

brienneoftarth.bio: Brienne is the sole surviving child and heir of Lord Selwyn Tarth of Evenfall Hall, on the island of Tarth.
brienneoftarth.name: Brienne of Tarth

lorastyrell.bio: The son of Lord Mace Tyrell and heir to Highgarden, Loras is a popular tourney knight and ranks as one of the most skilled knights in Westeros.
lorastyrell.name: Loras Tyrell

marei.bio: A prostitute in the King's Landing brothel owned by Petyr "Littlefinger" Baelish.
marei.name: Marei

edmuretully.bio: The younger brother of Catelyn and Lysa. He remains a hostage of Lord Frey.
edmuretully.name: Edmure Tully

bryndentully.bio: A respected knight and a member of House Tully. He is the younger brother of Lord Hoster Tully, and the uncle of Catelyn, Lysa, and Edmure Tully. He narrowly escaped the Red Wedding massacre while relieving himself on a tree outside.
bryndentully.name: Brynden Tully

meerareed.bio: Meera is the eldest child and only daughter of Lord Howland Reed of Greywater Watch. Her sole sibling is her younger brother Jojen Reed, who was killed by wights. She follows Leaf with Bran and Hodor to meet the three-eyed raven.
meerareed.name: Meera Reed

melessatarly.bio: The wife Lord Randyll Tarly of Horn Hill and mother of Samwell Tarly of the Night's Watch.
melessatarly.name: Melessa Tarly

waif.bio: The Waif is an acolyte of the Faceless Men serving in the House of Black and White in Braavos.
waif.name: The Waif

osha.bio: Osha is a woman of the Free Folk (or "wildling"), now in service to House Stark of Winterfell. Osha is currently escorting Rickon Stark to Last Hearth to seek refuge with House Umber.
osha.name: Osha

myrcellabaratheon.bio: Commonly thought to be the only daughter of King Robert Baratheon and Queen Cersei Lannister.
myrcellabaratheon.name: Myrcella Baratheon

izembaro.bio: Izembaro is the manager of a Braavosi troupe of actors, in which he also acts. Larger-than-life, he specializes in portraying drunken aristocrats. Huge presence on stage and rather nasty to his company when off-stage.
izembaro.name: Izembaro

lancel.bio: After sustaining heavy injuries during the Battle of the Blackwater, he joins the religious movement known as Sparrows and abandons his family name, after which he is simply known as Brother Lancel.
lancel.name: Lancel

nymeriasand.bio: The second of the eight bastard daughters of Prince Oberyn Martell, known as the "Sand Snakes". Very skilled with using her 8 foot long bullwhip in combat. Nymeria inherited her father's cunning, and is the most observant and calculating of the Sand Snakes.
nymeriasand.name: Nymeria Sand

bronn.bio: Bronn is a skilled and dangerous sellsword who comes to prominence when he champions for Tyrion Lannister in his trial by combat in the Eyrie. Poisoned by Tyene Sand and almost dies, but survives and is allowed to leave Dorne.
bronn.name: Bronn

lotharfrey.bio: Lothar is a son of Walder Frey, the Lord of the Crossing. He is the steward of the Twins, managing the day-to-day running of the castle. He often plans and organizes the fine details to achieve his father's goals.
lotharfrey.name: Lothar Frey

missandei.bio: A slave who served as an interpreter to the masters of Astapor, Missandei was freed by Daenerys and now serves as her trusted advisor and Handmaiden.
missandei.name: Missandei

melisandre.bio: Beautiful sorceress serves mysterious deity the Lord of Light and wields a variety of dubious magical powers.
melisandre.name: Melisandre

olly.bio: He was originally a farm boy at the Gift, but flees to the Night's Watch after his village is attacked by wildlings. Olly finishes Jon off by stabbing him through the chest, ending the mutiny and leaving his Lord Commander dead in the snow.
olly.name: Olly

kevanlannister.bio: Kevan is the younger brother of Lord Tywin Lannister and one of his most loyal and trusted officers in the Lannister armies during the War of the Five Kings, respected for his wise and candid counsel.
kevanlannister.name: Kevan Lannister

ellariasand.bio: Obara Sand is the eldest of the "Sand Snakes", the eight bastard daughters of Prince Oberyn Martell, and was named in honor of her father. Her mother was a peasant.
ellariasand.name: Ellaria Sand

haraldkarstark.bio: After the execution of Lord Rickard Karstark by Robb Stark, Harald is the new head of House Karstark and Lord of Karhold. He is described as ruthless and calculating.
haraldkarstark.name: Harald Karstark

sansastark.bio: Sansa Stark is the eldest daughter and second child of Lady Catelyn and Lord Eddard Stark. Held captive by Ramsay Bolton as his wife, she has escaped Winterfell with Theon by jumping off one of the walls.
sansastark.name: Sansa Stark

roosebolton.bio: Lord of Dreadfort, current King of the North after usurping the position from House Stark.
roosebolton.name: Roose Bolton

jorahmormont.bio: Ser Jorah is an exiled Northern lord living in Essos. He has sworn fealty to his fellow exile Daenerys Targaryen, but also a deep love for Daenerys
jorahmormont.name: Jorah Mormont

areohotah.bio: Captain of the Martell guard and the personal bodyguard of Prince Doran Martell, the ruler of Dorne. Renowned for his skill with the halberd.
areohotah.name: Areo Hotah

olennatyrell.bio: Queen of Thorns, holding a great deal of influence over the Reach. A widow of Lord Luthor Tyrell.
olennatyrell.name: Olenna Tyrell

balongreyjoy.bio: Hard, ambitious, and ruthless Lord Reaper of Pyke and head of House Greyjoy. Father of Theon and Yara Grejoy.
balongreyjoy.name: Balon Greyjoy

moro.bio: A Dothraki Khal, briefly appearing in the first novel in which he attends the wedding of Khal Drogo and Daenerys Targaryen.
moro.name: Moro

jaimelannister.bio: A knight of the Kingsguard, the eldest son of Tywin Lannister, younger twin brother of Queen Cersei Lannister, and older brother of Tyrion Lannister.
jaimelannister.name: Jaime Lannister

gregorclegane.bio: He is the head of House Clegane, the older brother of Sandor Clegane, and a notoriously fearsome warrior with a tendency toward extreme violence. Due to his freakishly huge size, he is called "The Mountain That Rides" or more so often simply "The Mountain".
gregorclegane.name: Gregor Clegane

thoros.bio: Thoros is a red priest of the Lord of Light and a noted warrior. Raised to become a Red Priest, though he grew up a gluttonous and lustful man, constantly raiding the kitchens and taking girls to his chambers.
thoros.name: Thoros

robinarryn.bio: Still being breastfed by his mother, despite approaching his teens, and takes a sick delight in seeing people thrown from the Eyrie's Moon Door.
robinarryn.name: Robin Arryn

ramsaybolton.bio: Sadistic bastard son of Roose Bolton, recently legitimized and thus, lawful heir to Winterfell and the North
ramsaybolton.name: Ramsay Bolton

randylltarly.bio: He is the Lord of Horn Hill and the head of House Tarly. He forced his son Samwell Tarly to join the Night's Watch under the threat of death. Fierce, ruthless warrior and a highly effective general.
randylltarly.name: Randyll Tarly

greyworm.bio: The chosen commander of the Unsullied, the warrior-eunuchs of Astapor whose reputation for combat is without equal.
greyworm.name: Grey Worm

podrickpayne.bio: Podrick Payne was Tyrion Lannister's squire and saved his life in the Battle of the Blackwater, but following Tyrion's arrest for the murder of King Joffrey Baratheon, he has since been given to Brienne of Tarth, who he joins on a quest to find Arya and Sansa Stark.
podrickpayne.name: Podrick Payne

daarionaharis.bio: The captain of the sellsword company, the Second Sons, and ally to Daenerys Targaryen.
daarionaharis.name: Daario Naharis

nightsking.bio: Leader of the White Walkers. He was a fearless warrior named the thirteenth Lord Commander of the Night's Watch.
nightsking.name: The Night's King

trystanemartell.bio: The youngest son of Prince Doran Martell, Lord of Sunspear and Prince of Dorne. Like his father Doran, Trystane lacks (for the most part) the hotheadedness typical of Dornishmen, as evidenced by his showing mercy to Bronn for attacking him.
trystanemartell.name: Trystane Martell

wunwun.bio: He is a wildling Giant who resided at Hardhome before being saved by Jon Snow and taken south of the Wall.  He is more commonly referred to by the other wildlings as "Wun Wun".
wunwun.name: Wun Wun

othellyarwyck.bio: Othell Yarwyck is the First Builder; a senior position within the Night's Watch, tasked with organizing the builders in maintaining The Wall. Second person to stab Jon Snow.
othellyarwyck.name: Othell Yarwyck

qyburn.bio: He is an unethical former maester who was thrown out of the order for conducting illegal human experimentation. While his unethical experiments have led to him being reviled, they also made him arguably one of the most talented healers in all of Westeros.
qyburn.name: Qyburn

obarasand.bio: The eldest of the "Sand Snakes", eight bastard daughters of Oberyn Martell. Even more than her sisters, Obara inherited her father's martial prowess, particularly his skill with a spear, and charges head-on into a situation, relying on brute strength.
obarasand.name: Obara Sand

theongreyjoy.bio: Only living son and heir of Lord Balon Greyjoy of the Iron Islands. Currently slave to Ramsay Bolton after exensive torture.
theongreyjoy.name: Theon Greyjoy

shae.bio: Shae is a prostitute who has begun an exclusive relationship with Tyrion Lannister during the time when he was fighting in the Lannister army as part of the Vanguard during the Battle of the Green Fork.
shae.name: Shae

rickonstark.bio: He is the youngest child and third son of Eddard and Catelyn Stark. Currently believed to be dead, but is being escorted by Usha to the Last Hearth to seek refuge with House Umber..
rickonstark.name: Rickon Stark

alliserthorne.bio: Castle Black's master-of-arms and a literal Thorne in Jon Snow's side from the moment he arrived at the Wall. Thorne was the first to stab Jon and leave him for dead.
alliserthorne.name: Alliser Thorne

tommenbaratheon.bio: Publicly, the youngest son of Kind Robert Baratheon and Queen Cersei Lannister, Tommen is good-natured and passive in contrast to his brother Joffrey, who sometimes bullied Tommen for amusement.  Like his sister, he is fond of his uncle Tyrion Lannister.
tommenbaratheon.name: Tommen Baratheon

eddisontollett.bio: Eddison Tollett is a brother of the Night's Watch and close friends with Jon Snow, Samwell Tarly, Grenn, and Pypar. Present alongside Jon Snow and the Night's Watch survivors returning to Castle Black after the fight against the White Walkers at Hardhome
eddisontollett.name: Eddison Tollett

pycelle.bio: Grand Maester. Member of the King's Council. Uses his old age and meek demeanour as a cloak to mask a sharp intellect and scheming nature which has allowed him to survive three kings.
pycelle.name: Pycelle

eurongreyjoy.bio: Euron is the younger brother of King Balon Greyjoy, older brother of Aeron Greyjoy, and the eldest uncle of Theon and Yara Greyjoy.
eurongreyjoy.name: Euron Greyjoy

margaerytyrell.bio: Margaery is the only daughter of Lady Alerie Tyrell and Lord Mace Tyrell. As beautiful as she is clever, her strength is in her ability to win the minds and loyalties of her subjects, and Kings.
margaerytyrell.name: Margaery Tyrell
